sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/System
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as Kueue Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>K8s API mTLS
    participant Controller as Kueue Controller<br/>Service Account Token
    participant VisAPI as Visibility API Server<br/>8082/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>Bearer Token
    participant RemoteAPI as Remote K8s API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+

    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over User,Controller: Flow 1: Job Submission and Queueing
        User->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/batch/v1/jobs<br/>User credentials
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-batch-v1-job<br/>TLS 1.2+ K8s API mTLS
        Webhook->>K8sAPI: Validate LocalQueue exists<br/>Service Account Token
        K8sAPI-->>Webhook: LocalQueue found
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutate response (add queue label)
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-batch-v1-job<br/>TLS 1.2+ K8s API mTLS
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation response (allow)
        K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: Job created<br/>Service Account Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Workload CR<br/>Service Account Token
        K8sAPI-->>User: Job created (suspended)
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Controller,K8sAPI: Flow 2: Workload Admission
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch ClusterQueue resources<br/>Service Account Token
        K8sAPI-->>Controller: ClusterQueue has quota available
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Workload (pending)<br/>Service Account Token
        K8sAPI-->>Controller: Workload queued
        Controller->>Controller: Run admission checks<br/>(AdmissionCheck CRs)
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Update Workload status (admitted)<br/>Service Account Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Update Job (unsuspend)<br/>Service Account Token
        K8sAPI-->>Controller: Job running
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Update ClusterQueue quota<br/>Service Account Token
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over Prometheus,Controller: Flow 3: Metrics Collection
        Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Bearer Token
        Controller-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics<br/>(queue depth, resource usage, admission latency)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 255)
        Note over User,VisAPI: Flow 4: Visibility API Query
        User->>K8sAPI: GET /apis/visibility.kueue.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1<br/>User credentials
        K8sAPI->>VisAPI: Forward request<br/>8082/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Service Account Token
        VisAPI->>K8sAPI: Query pending workloads<br/>Service Account Token
        K8sAPI-->>VisAPI: Workload list
        VisAPI-->>K8sAPI: Pending workload summary
        K8sAPI-->>User: JSON response
    end

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Controller,RemoteAPI: Flow 5: Multi-Cluster Job Distribution (MultiKueue)
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch MultiKueueCluster CR<br/>Service Account Token
        K8sAPI-->>Controller: Remote cluster config
        Controller->>RemoteAPI: Create Workload on remote cluster<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Kubeconfig credentials
        RemoteAPI-->>Controller: Workload admitted
        Controller->>RemoteAPI: Watch remote Workload status<br/>Kubeconfig credentials
        RemoteAPI-->>Controller: Workload completed
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Update local Workload status<br/>Service Account Token
    end
